beer.beer_description:
A beer born in a moment.  
James Kendall of Small 
Acres Cyder Orange was
sitting in a cosy English 
pub last Christmas drinking 
a nut brown ale and eating
cherries and chocolate. 
The result? 3 producers 
from Orange, NSW have 
collaborated to bring 
you "Dark side of Orange" 
a Cherry and Chocolate 
Nut Brown Ale. With 
handpicked cherries from
the Small Acres orchard, 
PNG grown Cacao, 
hand-roasted in Orange by 
Origin Chocolate united 
with a rich, smooth,  nut 
brown ale brewed at 
Badlands Brewery.  Serve 
at 10-14c and enjoy with 
Black Forest Gateaux or 
something equally indulgent

items.badge_description: Looking for more kick than a session beer, but want to be able to stay for a few rounds? You have to keep it in the middle. That's 340 beers with an ABV greater than 5% and less than 10%.  Try 5 more for Level 69!

What happens when you take two or more amazing breweries, throw them into the tank and let them ferment together? An amazing collaboration beer, that’s what! Cheers to working together to create the perfect flavor. That's 25 different beers that have been brewed as a collaboration. Try 5 more for Level 6!

items.checkin_comment: A very exciting enjoyable beer. Easy to drink. Would be great with a dark cherry chocolate desert

items.badge_description: There's beer in them thar hills! You're setting off on your journey through the world of beer, but be sure to take a little time to get to know each brewery as you go. That's a beer from 110 different breweries. Try 5 more for Level 23!

Round and round the wheel goes! Which style you’ll be drinking, nobody knows! Your desire to explore different styles is inspiring. Keep it up! That's a check-in to at least 105 different styles. Try 5 more for Level 22!
